It looks like the `--xpath` option has been outputting newlines since 2.9.9. That was merged in [here](https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/libxml2/commit/da35eeae5b92b88d8ebdb64b4b327ac1c2cf1bce), it looks like for 2.9.9-rc1 or thereabouts.

The `--xpath0` option would be nice, too, but since there are now merge conflicts with the base branch, if there's no interest in re-basing the changes to implement that, perhaps it's best to just close this MR. In the interest of good housekeeping.

@cykerway It's kind of a shame that this didn't get merged in, but if it's any consolation _I'll_ always remember that you were the one who made `xmllint` great again. For me, anyway. <tt>;)</tt>

